054/**
055 * A {@link Constable}, immutable, sorted set of key-value pairs that
056 * can be used to further qualify an object for many different
057 * purposes.
058 *
059 * <p>Keys are sorted according to their natural order.</p>
060 *
061 * <p>This is a <a
062 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based
063 * class</a>.</p>
064 *
065 * <p>Values of type {@code K} must be members of classes adhering to
066 * <a
067 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based
068 * semantics</a>.</p>
069 *
070 * <p>Values of type {@code V} must be members of classes adhering to
071 * <a
072 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based
073 * semantics</a>.</p>
074 *
075 * <p>Undefined behavior will result if the preceding requirements are
076 * not honored.</p>
077 *
078 * @param <K> the type borne by the keys of the qualifiers in this
079 * {@link Qualifiers}
080 *
081 * @param <V> the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in this
082 * {@link Qualifiers}
083 *
084 * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson"
085 * target="_parent">Laird Nelson</a>
086 *
087 * @see #of(Constable, Constable)
088 */
089public final class Qualifiers<K extends Constable & Comparable<K>, V extends Constable> implements Constable, Iterable<Entry<K, V>> {
090
091
092  /*
093   * Static fields.
094   */
095
096
097  private static final Qualifiers<?, ?> EMPTY_QUALIFIERS = new Qualifiers<>();
098
099
100  /*
101   * Instance fields.
102   */
103
104
105  private final SortedMap<K, V> qualifiers;
106
107
108  /*
109   * Constructors.
110   */
111
112
113  /**
114   * Creates a new {@linkplain Map#isEmpty() empty} {@link
115   * Qualifiers}.
116   */
117  public Qualifiers() {
118    this(null);
119  }
120
121  /**
122   * Creates a new {@link Qualifiers}.
123   *
124   * @param qualifiers a {@link Map} representing the qualifiers; may be
125   * {@code null} in which case an {@linkplain Map#isEmpty() empty
126   * <code>Map</code>} will be used instead
127   */
128  public Qualifiers(final Map<? extends K, ? extends V> qualifiers) {
129    if (qualifiers == null || qualifiers.isEmpty()) {
130      this.qualifiers = emptySortedMap();
131    } else {
132      this.qualifiers = unmodifiableSortedMap(new TreeMap<>(qualifiers));
133    }
134  }

212  /**
213   * Returns {@code true} if this {@link Qualifiers} logically
214   * contains the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
215   *
216   * <p>A {@link Qualifiers} is said to contain another {@link
217   * Qualifiers} if either:</p>
218   *
219   * <ul>
220   *
221   * <li>the two {@link Qualifiers} instances are identical, or</li>
222   *
223   * <li>the {@linkplain Map#size() size} of the first {@link Qualifiers}
224   * is greater than the {@linkplain Map#size() size} of the second
225   * {@link Qualifiers}, and the {@linkplain Map#entrySet() entry set}
226   * of this {@link Qualifiers} {@linkplain
227   * Set#containsAll(java.util.Collection) contains all} of the
228   * entries in the second {@link Qualifiers}' {@linkplain
229   * Map#entrySet() entry set}</li>
230   *
231   * </ul>
232   *
233   * @param other the {@link Qualifiers} to test; must not be {@code
234   * null}
235   *
236   * @return {@code true} if this {@link Qualifiers} logically
237   * contains the supplied {@link Qualifiers}
238   *
239   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code other} is {@code null}
240   *
241   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
242   *
243   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
244   * threads.
245   *
246   * @see Map#size()
247   *
248   * @see Set#containsAll(java.util.Collection)
249   */
250  public final boolean contains(final Qualifiers<?, ?> other) {
251    return this == other || this.qualifiers.size() >= other.qualifiers.size() && this.qualifiers.entrySet().containsAll(other.qualifiers.entrySet());
252  }
253
254  /**
255   * Returns {@code true} if and only if this {@link Qualifiers}
256   * logically contains an entry equal to the supplied {@link Entry}.
257   *
258   * @param e the {@link Entry} to test; may be {@code null} in which
259   * case {@code false} will be returned
260   *
261   * @return {@code true} if and only if this {@link Qualifiers}
262   * logically contains an entry equal to the supplied {@link Entry}
263   *
264   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
265   *
266   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
267   * threads.
268   */
269  public final boolean contains(final Entry<?, ?> e) {
270    final Object v = e == null ? null : this.qualifiers.get(e.getKey());
271    return v != null && v.equals(e.getValue());
272  }

285   *

314  /**
315   * Returns {@code true} if and only if this {@link Qualifiers} is a
316   * subset of the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
317   *
318   * @param other the other {@link Qualifiers}; must not be {@code
319   * null}
320   *
321   * @return {@code true} if and only if this {@link Qualifiers} is a
322   * subset of the supplied {@link Qualifiers}
323   *
324   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code other} is {@code null}
325   *
326   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
327   *
328   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
329   * threads.
330   */
331  public final boolean isSubsetOf(final Qualifiers<?, ?> other) {
332    return other == this || other.contains(this);
333  }

335  /**
336   * Returns the number of entries this {@link Qualifiers} has in
337   * common with the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
338   *
339   * <p>The number returned will be {@code 0} or greater.</p>
340   *
341   * @param other the other {@link Qualifiers}; may be {@code null} in
342   * which case {@code 0} will be returned
343   *
344   * @return the number of entries this {@link Qualifiers} has in
345   * common with the supplied {@link Qualifiers}
346   *
347   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
348   *
349   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
350   * threads.
351   */
352  public final int intersectionSize(final Qualifiers<?, ?> other) {
353    if (other == this) {
354      // Just an identity check to rule this easy case out.
355      return this.qualifiers.size();
356    } else if (other == null || other.qualifiers.isEmpty()) {
357      return 0;
358    } else {
359      final Collection<? extends Entry<?, ?>> otherEntrySet = other.qualifiers.entrySet();
360      return (int)this.qualifiers.entrySet()
361        .stream()
362        .filter(otherEntrySet::contains)
363        .count();
364    }
365  }
366
367  /**
368   * Returns the size of the <em>symmetric difference</em> between
369   * this {@link Qualifiers} and the supplied {@link Qualifiers}.
370   *
371   * <p>The number returned is always {@code 0} or greater.</p>
372   *
373   * <p>The size of the symmetric difference between two {@link
374   * Qualifiers} instances is the number of qualifier entries that are
375   * in one {@link Qualifiers} instance but not in the other.</p>
376   *
377   * @param other the other {@link Qualifiers} instance; may be {@code
378   * null}
379   *
380   * @return the size of the <em>symmetric difference</em> between
381   * this {@link Qualifiers} and the supplied {@link Qualifiers};
382   * always {@code 0} or greater
383   *
384   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
385   *
386   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
387   * threads.
388   */
389  public final int symmetricDifferenceSize(final Qualifiers<?, ?> other) {
390    if (other == this) {
391      // Just an identity check to rule this easy case out.
392      return 0;
393    } else if (other == null || other.qualifiers.isEmpty()) {
394      return this.qualifiers.size();
395    } else if (this.equals(other)) {
396      return 0;
397    } else {
398      final Collection<Entry<?, ?>> otherSymmetricDifference = new HashSet<>(this.qualifiers.entrySet());
399      other.qualifiers.entrySet().stream()
400        .filter(Predicate.not(otherSymmetricDifference::add))
401        .forEach(otherSymmetricDifference::remove);
402      return otherSymmetricDifference.size();
403    }
404  }

406  /**
407   * Returns an {@link Optional} containing a {@link ConstantDesc}
408   * representing this {@link Qualifiers}.
409   *
410   * @return an {@link Optional} containing a {@link ConstantDesc}
411   * representing this {@link Qualifiers}; never {@code null}; never
412   * {@linkplain Optional#isEmpty() empty}
413   *
414   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
415   *
416   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
417   *
418   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
419   * threads.
420   */
421  @Override // Constable
422  public final Optional<? extends ConstantDesc> describeConstable() {
423    final Collection<Entry<K, V>> entrySet = this.qualifiers.entrySet();
424    if (entrySet.isEmpty()) {
425      return
426        Optional.of(DynamicConstantDesc.ofNamed(BSM_INVOKE,
427                                                DEFAULT_NAME,
428                                                CD_Qualifiers,
429                                                MethodHandleDesc.ofMethod(STATIC,
430                                                                          CD_Qualifiers,
431                                                                          "of",
432                                                                          MethodTypeDesc.of(CD_Qualifiers))));
433    } else {
434      final int bsmInvokeArgumentsLength = 2 * entrySet.size() + 1;
435      final ConstantDesc[] bsmInvokeArguments = new ConstantDesc[bsmInvokeArgumentsLength];
436      bsmInvokeArguments[0] =
437        MethodHandleDesc.ofMethod(STATIC,
438                                  CD_Qualifiers,
439                                  "of",
440                                  MethodTypeDesc.of(CD_Qualifiers,
441                                                    CD_Constable.arrayType()));
442      int i = 1;
443      for (final Entry<K, V> entry : entrySet) {
444        final Constable key = entry.getKey();
445        final ConstantDesc k = key == null ? null : key.describeConstable().orElse(null);
446        if (k == null) {
447          return Optional.empty();
448        }
449        bsmInvokeArguments[i++] = k;
450        final Constable value = entry.getValue();
451        final ConstantDesc v = value == null ? NULL : value.describeConstable().orElse(null);
452        if (v == null) {
453          return Optional.empty();
454        }
455        bsmInvokeArguments[i++] = v;
456      }
457      return Optional.of(DynamicConstantDesc.ofNamed(BSM_INVOKE,
458                                                     DEFAULT_NAME,
459                                                     CD_Qualifiers,
460                                                     bsmInvokeArguments));
461    }
462  }

481  /**
482   * Returns {@code true} if this {@link Qualifiers} is equal to the
483   * supplied {@link Object}.
484   *
485   * @param other the object to test; may be {@code null} in which
486   * case {@code false} will be returned
487   *
488   * @return {@code true} if this {@link Qualifiers} is equal to the
489   * supplied {@link Object}; {@code false} otherwise
490   *
491   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
492   *
493   * @threadsafety This method is safe  for concurrent use by multiple
494   * threads.
495   */
496  @Override // Object
497  public final boolean equals(final Object other) {
498    if (other == this) {
499      return true;
500    } else if (other != null && other.getClass() == this.getClass()) {
501      final Qualifiers<?, ?> her = (Qualifiers<?, ?>)other;
502      return
503        Objects.equals(this.qualifiers, her.qualifiers);
504    } else {
505      return false;
506    }
507  }

528  /**
529   * Returns a <strong>new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose keys are
530   * produced by the supplied {@link Function}, which is expected to
531   * prepend a prefix to the original key and return the result.
532   *
533   * @param <K2> the type borne by the new keys
534   *
535   * @param f a non-{@code null}, deterministic, idempotent {@link
536   * Function} that accepts keys drawn from this {@link Qualifiers}'
537   * {@linkplain Map#entrySet() entry set} and returns a non-{@code
538   * null} prefixed version of that key; must not be {@code null}
539   *
540   * @return a <strong>new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose keys have
541   * been prefixed by the actions of the supplied {@link Function}
542   *
543   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code f} is {@code null}
544   *
545   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
546   *
547   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic,
548   * assuming the supplied {@link Function} is.
549   *
550   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
551   * threads, assuming the supplied {@link Function} is
552   */
553  public final <K2 extends Constable & Comparable<K2>> Qualifiers<K2, V> withPrefix(final Function<? super K, ? extends K2> f) {
554    final Map<K2, V> map = new TreeMap<>();
555    for (final Entry<? extends K, ? extends V> entry : this.qualifiers.entrySet()) {
556      map.put(f.apply(entry.getKey()), entry.getValue());
557    }
558    return new Qualifiers<>(map);
559  }

661  /**
662   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers} consisting of the entries
663   * represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs.
664   *
665   * @param <K> the type borne by the keys of the qualifiers in the
666   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
667   *
668   * @param <V> the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in the
669   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
670   *
671   * @param name0 a qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
672   *
673   * @param value0 the qualifier value corresponding to the
674   * immediately preceding qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
675   *
676   * @param name1 a qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
677   *
678   * @param value1 the qualifier value corresponding to the
679   * immediately preceding qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
680   *
681   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} consisting of the entries
682   * represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs
683   *
684   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
685   *
686   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
687   *
688   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
689   * threads.
690   */
691  public static final <K extends Constable & Comparable<K>, V extends Constable> Qualifiers<K, V> of(final K name0, final V value0,
692                                                                                                     final K name1, final V value1) {
693    return new Qualifiers<>(Map.of(name0, value0, name1, value1));
694  }

696  /**
697   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers} consisting of the entries
698   * represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs.
699   *
700   * @param <K> the type borne by the keys of the qualifiers in the
701   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
702   *
703   * @param <V> the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in the
704   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
705   *
706   * @param name0 a qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
707   *
708   * @param value0 the qualifier value corresponding to the
709   * immediately preceding qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
710   *
711   * @param name1 a qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
712   *
713   * @param value1 the qualifier value corresponding to the
714   * immediately preceding qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
715   *
716   * @param name2 a qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
717   *
718   * @param value2 the qualifier value corresponding to the
719   * immediately preceding qualifier name; must not be {@code null}
720   *
721   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} consisting of the entries
722   * represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs
723   *
724   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
725   *
726   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
727   *
728   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
729   * threads.
730   */
731  public static final <K extends Constable & Comparable<K>, V extends Constable> Qualifiers<K, V> of(final K name0, final V value0,
732                                                                                                     final K name1, final V value1,
733                                                                                                     final K name2, final V value2) {
734    return new Qualifiers<>(Map.of(name0, value0, name1, value1, name2, value2));
735  }

737  /**
738   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers} consisting of the entries
739   * represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs.
740   *
741   * <p>The supplied {@code nameValuePairs} must be an even-numbered
742   * array of non-{@code null} {@link Constable} instances, where the
743   * zero-based even-numbered elements are {@link String}s represents
744   * qualifier names, and the zero-based odd-numbered {@link
745   * Constable} elements represent qualifier values.</p>
746   *
747   * @param <K> the type borne by the keys of the qualifiers in the
748   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
749   *
750   * @param <V> the type borne by the values of the qualifiers in the
751   * returned {@link Qualifiers}
752   *
753   * @param nameValuePairs the name-value pairs as described above;
754   * may be {@code null} in which case the return value of the {@link
755   * #of()} method will be returned
756   *
757   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} consisting of the entries
758   * represented by the supplied alternating name-value pairs
759   *
760   * @exception IllegalArgumentException if an even number of
761   * arguments is not supplied
762   *
763   * @exception ClassCastException if elements in the supplied array
764   * at even positions ({@code 0}, {@code 2}, {@code 4}…) are not of
765   * type {@code K}
766   *
767   * @exception NullPointerException if any argument is {@code null}
768   *
769   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
770   *
771   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
772   *
773   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
774   * threads.
775   */
776  // Used by #describeConstable()
777  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
778  public static final <K extends Constable & Comparable<K>, V extends Constable> Qualifiers<K, V> of(final Constable... nameValuePairs) {
779    if (nameValuePairs == null || nameValuePairs.length <= 0) {
780      return of();
781    } else if (nameValuePairs.length % 2 != 0) {
782      throw new IllegalArgumentException("nameValuePairs: " + Arrays.toString(nameValuePairs));
783    } else {
784      final Map<K, V> map = new TreeMap<>();
785      for (int i = 0; i < nameValuePairs.length; i++) {
786        map.put((K)nameValuePairs[i++], (V)nameValuePairs[i]);
787      }
788      return new Qualifiers<>(map);
789    }
790  }
